        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44292",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The used number format depends on the set locale and the set format. It is correct.\r\nIf you like to get an integer instead of a localized number use the getValue() method which returns you a plain number.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-02-06T13:42:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-02-06T13:42:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44296",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=umpirsky",
                        "name": "umpirsky",
                        "displayName": "Sasa Stamenkovic",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "http:\/\/www.google.com\/search?q=22754856+bytes+in+MB\r\n\r\n22 754 856 bytes = 21.7007217 megabytes\r\n\r\nIt should round it on 2 decimals, and it should be around 22MB, but it says 1000000 times bigger value.\r\n\r\n22,754,856.0 MB (22754856)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=umpirsky",
                        "name": "umpirsky",
                        "displayName": "Sasa Stamenkovic",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-02-06T22:53:49.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-02-06T22:53:49.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44385",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "You want to give and output all numbers localized to sr_SR.\r\nBut then you use printf as verification which itself is non-localized.\r\n\r\nThis can not work:\r\nA number like \"12,000\" will be interpreted as 12000 in sr_SR.\r\nBut in en_US it would be interpreted as 12 (a floating value with a precision of 3).\r\n\r\ntoString() localized the output (as requested) but printf does not know about your localization-wish and works with the locale from your server (as it's a non-ZF method).\r\n\r\nTherefor this issue will not be reopened.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-02-16T03:26:33.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-02-16T03:26:33.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44387",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=umpirsky",
                        "name": "umpirsky",
                        "displayName": "Sasa Stamenkovic",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Ah, ok, so printf is producing this format, thanks.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=umpirsky",
                        "name": "umpirsky",
                        "displayName": "Sasa Stamenkovic",
                        "active": true
                    },
